From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Thu, 12 Feb 2026 12:45:48 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] phy: cix: usbdp: enable full PHY reset under ACPI

The ACPI path previously skipped PHY reset on the assumption that
firmware-initialized PHY state could be preserved.  Now that
cdnsp-sky1's drd_init runs for both DT and ACPI (resetting the USB
controller hardware), the PHY must be fully reinitialized to match.

Set phy_reset=true under ACPI, matching the DT ROLE_NONE behavior:
full reset and initialization when the consumer calls phy_set_mode().
---
 drivers/phy/cix/phy-cix-usbdp.c | 11 +++++++++--
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/cix/phy-cix-usbdp.c b/drivers/phy/cix/phy-cix-usbdp.c
index b9887d3e4e7f7..91dbc14473d03 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/cix/phy-cix-usbdp.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/cix/phy-cix-usbdp.c
@@ -1481,8 +1481,15 @@ static int cix_udphy_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	udphy->phy_init_skip_count = 0;
 
 	if (ACPI_COMPANION(dev)) {
-		udphy->phy_reset = false;
-		dev_info(dev, "ACPI boot: skipping PHY reset (firmware-initialized)\n");
+		/*
+		 * Under ACPI, firmware initializes PHYs for UEFI USB and
+		 * display.  However, cdnsp-sky1 drd_init() resets the USB
+		 * controller hardware, so we must reinitialize the PHY to
+		 * match.  Treat ACPI the same as the DT ROLE_NONE case:
+		 * full reset + init when the consumer calls phy_set_mode().
+		 */
+		udphy->phy_reset = true;
+		udphy->phy_init_skip_count = 0;
 	} else {
 		g_status = ioremap(GOP_STATUS_ADDRESS, GOP_STATUS_SIZE);
 		if (g_status) {
